      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pork is cooking, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon)and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim and slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Wash then cut the <strong>pak choi</strong> in half, separating the <strong>white base</strong> and <strong>green tops</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Chop the <strong>white bases </strong>into bite-size pieces & shred the <strong>green tops</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681305821417-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681305821417-x400.jpg",
