          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681305821417-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork has browned, add the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and half of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 2 min further</p><p>Once cooked, transfer everything to a bowl and set aside</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681305826819-x200.jpg",
